com.amplifyframework.core.model.annotations

Annotation Type HasMany


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=FIELD)
public @interface HasMany
    This annotation is used to indicate that a field is the owner of relationship to a list of entities that extend Model. The RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME annotation is added to retain ModelField at runtime for the reflection capabilities to work in order to check if this annotation is present for a field of a Model. ElementType.FIELD annotation is added to indicate ModelField annotation can be used only on Fields (Data members of a class).

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      java.lang.String associatedWith
      Returns the name of the corresponding field in the other model that is associated with this field.
      java.lang.Class<? extends Model> type
      Returns the target type of the foreign key model.
